data.value:
The information in the Atlas of Solar Resources is presented in various forms - interactive maps, output tables and graphs:
•	the resource maps – maps of long-term average annual values of solar radiation data;
•	the maps for assessing the potential of solar energy – maps of monthly averages of different types of radiation on differently oriented surfaces, monthly averages of the geometric parameters of the Sun (altitude, azimuth);
•	the climatic maps –  maps of basic meteorological characteristics;
•	the maps of solar energy facilities – a map with existing and projected solar energy facilities;
•	the maps of limitations and prerequisites for the location of solar energy facilities - maps of factors that favor or limit the deployment of solar energy facilities: 
	Specially protected natural areas of national importance;
	Archaeological monuments and other objects of historical and cultural heritage of international and republican significance;
	Territories of forest state institutions;
	Water reservoirs, water protection zones and watercourse strips;
	Power lines;
	Automobile roads;
	Human settlements;
•	auxiliary layers - digital relief model (DEM), terrain slopes, slope exposition, administrative-territorial division, meteorological stations of RSE "Kazhydromet"
Functionality of the Atlas of Solar Resources:
•	General functionality (selection and visualization of cartographic layers from the atlas set, selection of base layers, map navigation function, scaling, legend viewing, “identification” tool, measuring tool (distances, areas), viewing reference information about the cartographic layer;
•	Selecting and exporting data for the selected point (table, graph);
•	Comparison of the initial data on several selected points on the map (graphs, diagrams, tables);
•	Preliminary ranking of the suitability of the territory for the accommodation of solar energy facilities;
•	Calculator "The calculation of the PV system area" – the calculation of the areas of solar panels for the selected type of projected photovoltaic station;
•	Calculator "The calculation of the energy output of the PV system" – the calculation of the energy output of solar panels of the projected photovoltaic station of the selected type for the selected location;
•	Calculator "The calculation of energy consumption" - for the calculation of the total electricity consumption by household electrical appliances.
